1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:03,733
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:07,467 --> 00:00:09,900
- What are you doing?
- I saw a man earlier.

3
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:11,600
Something about his behavior
felt strange.

4
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:13,300
I have a really bad feeling
about it.

5
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:14,500
Maybe you were just
seeing things.

6
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:16,567
Walter, do you still
remember me?

7
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:17,867
Walter, please.

8
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,667
Help me save my family

9
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,833
from what Aldrin is planning
to do.

10
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:24,467
What are you doing?

11
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:26,333
We are not a perfect
Torrecampo family.

12
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:27,800
We have many flaws,

13
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:29,567
and many conflicts
among ourselves.

14
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:30,900
So starting today,

15
00:00:31,033 --> 00:00:33,500
we are going to rebuild our name

16
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:36,500
and our family
on a stronger foundation.

17
00:00:36,667 --> 00:00:39,500
- [APPLAUDING]
- [INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

18
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:42,000
[METAL CLANGING]

19
00:00:44,767 --> 00:00:47,633
- [PEOPLE SQUEALING]
- [METAL CLATTERS]

20
00:00:47,767 --> 00:00:50,867
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

21
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:34,833
Hello, Sir.

22
00:01:34,967 --> 00:01:36,200
Love.

23
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,933
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- What are you doing?

24
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,100
I saw a man earlier.

25
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:42,567
What?

26
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:44,000
A man?

27
00:01:44,133 --> 00:01:45,567
Where?

28
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:47,267
He was just over there earlier.

29
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,967
And his behavior seemed strange.

30
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:52,600
I have a bad feeling about it.

31
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:56,167
Love, our workers are
on lunch break right now.

32
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:57,467
Maybe you were just
imagining things.

33
00:01:57,600 --> 00:02:00,667
No, I'm sure about what I saw.

34
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,300
I don't feel good
about this right now.

35
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:04,900
Can we please not continue this?

36
00:02:05,033 --> 00:02:06,633
Maybe we do it another time?

37
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:09,000
Love, it's not going to be easy
to reschedule.

38
00:02:09,133 --> 00:02:10,833
Edward's timeline
will be affected.

39
00:02:10,967 --> 00:02:13,000
This is his comeback project.

40
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,933
It has to go as planned.

41
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:18,833
Okay, I'll coordinate
with security

42
00:02:18,967 --> 00:02:22,633
to make sure that no one
unauthorized has entered, okay?

43
00:02:22,767 --> 00:02:24,400
To make sure the area is safe.

44
00:02:25,433 --> 00:02:26,433
Come on.

45
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,633
Please come this way.

46
00:02:30,767 --> 00:02:33,067
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:41,633
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

48
00:03:11,433 --> 00:03:12,667
Walter?

49
00:03:14,733 --> 00:03:18,667
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

50
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:24,533
Do you still remember me?

51
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,800
What happened to you?

52
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,767
Was I also the reason why
you ended up like this?

53
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:36,967
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

54
00:03:42,167 --> 00:03:44,567
I'm so sorry, Walter.

55
00:03:46,133 --> 00:03:48,267
That I was the reason

56
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:51,700
your child with Catherine
grew resentful.

57
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:57,700
And I'm also so sorry that
I kept Paolo away from you.

58
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,333
But I'm so thankful.

59
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:05,800
Because of you, I have him.

60
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:12,167
He is one of the most beautiful
things in my life.

61
00:04:15,033 --> 00:04:18,067
But I also want to apologize
to you.

62
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:23,233
For letting you go so easily.

63
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:28,833
I could no longer live
with the guilt.

64
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:33,167
But our mistakes have come back
to haunt us.

65
00:04:35,533 --> 00:04:37,467
I can't blame...

66
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:40,433
your child for the anger
he feels.

67
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:43,733
But, Walter,

68
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:47,867
he is becoming dangerous.

69
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,167
He's doing things
to get back at me

70
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:53,300
and many people
are getting hurt.

71
00:04:55,233 --> 00:04:57,567
And I'm afraid
that he won't stop

72
00:04:57,700 --> 00:05:00,133
until my family is destroyed.

73
00:05:01,667 --> 00:05:03,533
So, Walter, please.

74
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:06,667
Help me.

75
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:11,933
Help me save my family from
what Aldrin is planning to do.

76
00:05:13,133 --> 00:05:17,067
Even for the sake of our child,
Paolo.

77
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,867
Please, Walter.

78
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:28,933
My father once said,

79
00:05:29,067 --> 00:05:32,500
an idea will remain just an idea

80
00:05:32,633 --> 00:05:34,267
if it's not brought to life.

81
00:05:34,433 --> 00:05:37,300
Like a soul without a body,

82
00:05:37,433 --> 00:05:39,967
a mind without a heart.

83
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:44,467
That's why I want to thank
all of our architects,

84
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,333
engineers,

85
00:05:46,467 --> 00:05:49,067
and all our construction
workers.

86
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:53,367
Because you are the ones
who bring this project to life.

87
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:56,433
[APPLAUDING]

88
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:06,100
Mr. Torrecampo,
what can you say to critics

89
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:09,567
who say that the Torrecampos
are not a good example?

90
00:06:09,733 --> 00:06:12,900
That people shouldn't follow
your example.

91
00:06:14,667 --> 00:06:16,033
Excuse me, I'm sorry,

92
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:19,433
but may we request
that we focus the questions

93
00:06:19,567 --> 00:06:21,433
on the construction project.

94
00:06:21,567 --> 00:06:23,300
<i> No, no, no, Gemma, it's okay.</i>

95
00:06:23,433 --> 00:06:25,200
<i>I'd like to answer
that question.</i>

96
00:06:26,433 --> 00:06:28,667
We are not a perfect,
the Torrecampo family.

97
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,200
We have many flaws,

98
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:32,700
many conflicts with one another.

99
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:37,367
As they say, our family is like
this building,

100
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:38,967
<i> already condemned.</i>

101
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,733
<i>But here's the thing
about construction.</i>

102
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:45,067
<i>You don't fix a rotten building.</i>

103
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,500
<i> You demolish it.</i>

104
00:06:47,967 --> 00:06:49,467
<i> So starting today,</i>

105
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,800
<i>we are tearing down
the old Torrecampo image.</i>

106
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:57,800
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:07:02,533 --> 00:07:05,433
Do you want to say something,
Walter?

108
00:07:05,567 --> 00:07:07,767
[WHIMPERING]

109
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:09,767
What is it? What is it?

110
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,867
<i>I want you to eliminate
Edward Torrecampo.</i>

111
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,167
<i> I'll handle it.</i>

112
00:07:24,233 --> 00:07:25,967
Walter?

113
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,700
What do you want to say?

114
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:28,833
[WHIMPERING]

115
00:07:28,967 --> 00:07:31,667
- What is it? I can't...
- What are you doing here?

116
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:38,233
- Aldrin.
- Who told you could come here?

117
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:41,233
Aldrin, I'm sorry.

118
00:07:41,367 --> 00:07:44,067
I know you hate me
and my family.

119
00:07:45,533 --> 00:07:47,867
I committed a wrongdoing,
your father and I,

120
00:07:48,033 --> 00:07:49,733
but believe me,

121
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:52,000
I've regretted it
for a long time.

122
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:55,067
Leave.

123
00:07:57,433 --> 00:07:58,900
Leave right now.

124
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:02,667
Aldrin, we've corrected
our mistakes.

125
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,967
We went back
to our respective spouses.

126
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,800
So please,
don't punish me anymore.

127
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:08,733
My mother took her own life

128
00:08:09,767 --> 00:08:11,467
because of your betrayal!

129
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,733
What you did is unforgivable!

130
00:08:19,067 --> 00:08:20,467
Blame me,

131
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,133
but please don't involve
my family.

132
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:24,500
They had nothing to do
with this.

133
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:27,233
There are consequences

134
00:08:27,367 --> 00:08:29,167
to what you both did.

135
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:33,133
And I will never stop

136
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:40,533
until you feel the pain I felt
when my mother died!

137
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:45,100
- Aldrin, please.
- Leave...

138
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:48,033
before I completely lose
my temper.

139
00:08:50,033 --> 00:08:51,767
Leave!

140
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:54,433
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

141
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:01,367
[WHIMPERING]

142
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:08,233
Including those who tried
to weaken the structure

143
00:09:08,367 --> 00:09:09,933
especially from the inside.

144
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:14,967
We are going to rebuild our name

145
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:18,600
and our family
on a stronger foundation.

146
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:20,300
Thank you very much
to all of you!

147
00:09:20,433 --> 00:09:22,700
- [APPLAUDING]
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

148
00:09:22,833 --> 00:09:26,867
- [APPLAUDING CONTINUES]
- [INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:38,200
Edward!

150
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,833
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

151
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:46,033
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

152
00:09:46,167 --> 00:09:49,167
[METAL CLANGING]

153
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:56,033
[SQUEALING]

154
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,500
[SQUEALS]

155
00:09:59,633 --> 00:10:01,100
[PAOLO EXCLAIMS]

156
00:10:07,667 --> 00:10:08,733
Edward, are you okay?

157
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:09,733
Are you all right?

158
00:10:09,867 --> 00:10:13,200
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

159
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:14,533
Edward?

160
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:24,467
Love, are you okay?

161
00:10:25,967 --> 00:10:27,867
Marj, Paolo,

162
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,333
thank you.

163
00:10:29,467 --> 00:10:31,267
If you hadn't helped me,

164
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,367
I'd be dead by now.

165
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,433
I'm just glad you're okay.

166
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,633
You're like a sibling to me now.

167
00:10:37,767 --> 00:10:40,100
I won't let anything happen
to you.

168
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,167
Gemma.

169
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:45,367
Sir?

170
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:47,633
Make sure there's a news
blackout on what happened today.

171
00:10:47,767 --> 00:10:50,000
Until the investigation
is finished.

172
00:10:50,133 --> 00:10:52,267
It could ruin the project
if this gets out.

173
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:54,000
- Okay, Sir.
- Thank you.

174
00:10:55,433 --> 00:10:56,400
Thank you.

175
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:02,333
Sir, believe me, we left the
gantry crane properly secured.

176
00:11:02,467 --> 00:11:04,533
We were on break,
so no one else was there.

177
00:11:04,667 --> 00:11:07,467
I honestly don't know how those
steel beams fell down there.

178
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:09,700
What?

179
00:11:10,733 --> 00:11:13,833
Could it be that the man
did this?

180
00:11:13,967 --> 00:11:17,267
Maybe he's the one
who wants to hurt Edward?

181
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:18,700
What man?

182
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:21,767
Marj and I think
there was an outsider

183
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,667
who entered the premises.

184
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:25,867
I already alerted
our security team.

185
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,633
But they didn't find anyone.

186
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,400
Did someone sneak in
or was let in?

187
00:11:30,533 --> 00:11:32,033
Could someone have ordered
someone to come in

188
00:11:32,167 --> 00:11:33,633
to attempt to kill me?

189
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:38,667
Who here hates you enough
to do something like that?

190
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:42,200
Excuse me?

191
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:44,100
I have nothing to do with this.

192
00:11:44,233 --> 00:11:46,233
I also rely on this project.

193
00:11:46,367 --> 00:11:50,267
So I wouldn't allow anything bad
to happen to Edward either.

194
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:57,033
There's one more person
who could be behind this.

195
00:11:57,167 --> 00:11:58,800
Aldrin Castelo.

196
00:11:58,933 --> 00:12:00,667
Doesn't he have intense hatred
toward our family

197
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:01,933
because of mom?

198
00:12:02,067 --> 00:12:03,800
Because he was removed
from the company?

199
00:12:05,233 --> 00:12:06,800
He most likely has something
to do with this.

200
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:11,167
There's only one way to be sure.

201
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,100
You need to catch the person
my spouse saw.

202
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:22,033
Only that person can point us
to who really initiated this.

203
00:12:22,167 --> 00:12:23,933
- Yes, Sir.
- Thank you very much.

204
00:12:24,067 --> 00:12:26,700
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

205
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:35,500
Useless!
[THUDS]

206
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:38,000
You had one job!

207
00:12:39,033 --> 00:12:41,367
Sir, one more chance, Sir.

208
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,900
Please give me another chance.

209
00:12:44,567 --> 00:12:46,833
Because of your failure,

210
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:49,100
they'll be more careful now!

211
00:12:49,267 --> 00:12:51,067
I won't be able to get close
to Edward anymore!

212
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,133
But, Sir...

213
00:12:52,267 --> 00:12:53,900
Sir.

214
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:55,133
- [THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

215
00:12:55,267 --> 00:12:58,733
I don't give second chances!

216
00:12:58,867 --> 00:13:01,567
Especially to people
who ruin my plans!

217
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:02,900
- [THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

218
00:13:03,033 --> 00:13:04,933
[THUDDING]

219
00:13:13,867 --> 00:13:16,700
It's a good thing that
you weren't seriously injured.

220
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:19,333
I couldn't handle it
if you were badly hurt.

221
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:24,533
You know, there's only one
person I think is behind this.

222
00:13:24,667 --> 00:13:26,000
Aldrin.

223
00:13:26,133 --> 00:13:30,033
I'm sure he ordered the attempt
on your life.

224
00:13:30,167 --> 00:13:32,333
That's what we think too.

225
00:13:32,467 --> 00:13:33,900
That's why I ordered
for the person

226
00:13:34,033 --> 00:13:36,500
who attempted on your life
to be found, Edward.

227
00:13:36,633 --> 00:13:39,800
We just need solid proof
or a witness

228
00:13:39,933 --> 00:13:41,867
so we can finally arrest Aldrin.

229
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,433
I'll make sure he's found.

230
00:13:44,567 --> 00:13:46,333
That man will pay.

231
00:13:47,367 --> 00:13:52,033
Maybe we can postpone the
Thanksgiving dinner tomorrow?

232
00:13:52,167 --> 00:13:54,500
Until the one responsible
is caught?

233
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:57,167
This shouldn't affect our plans.

234
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:59,133
We're still pushing through
with the event.

235
00:13:59,267 --> 00:14:01,467
Dad, it's not safe!

236
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,333
You almost died out there!

237
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:08,167
Uncle Edward, we can celebrate
it at a later date.

238
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:10,833
I don't want to show
the person behind this

239
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:14,867
that they've won because
we're scared and backing down.

240
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:18,767
But, my child,
we're still scared.

241
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:21,067
What, do we wait for something
worse to happen?

242
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,133
Your mom is right, Edward.

243
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:25,867
We shouldn't be afraid.

244
00:14:27,133 --> 00:14:31,333
We need to prove to that person
that we're solid.

245
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:32,667
United.

246
00:14:33,733 --> 00:14:36,933
And we won't easily give in
to his death threats,

247
00:14:37,067 --> 00:14:38,800
or his intimidation.

248
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:43,467
Edward has a point.

249
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:47,300
There are other ways to ensure
the family's safety.

250
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:50,433
I'll talk to the organizers
to tighten our security

251
00:14:50,567 --> 00:14:52,933
so that no one unfamiliar
can enter.

252
00:14:53,067 --> 00:14:55,867
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:14:56,967 --> 00:14:58,300
Are you sure?

254
00:14:59,267 --> 00:15:01,667
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

255
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:07,400
Hey, it's you, isn't it?

256
00:15:08,767 --> 00:15:11,300
You're the one who ordered
Edward to be killed, right?

257
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:16,733
You said you wouldn't go
through with your plan.

258
00:15:16,867 --> 00:15:18,367
So why did you still do it?

259
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:21,833
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

260
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:24,533
What are you going to do?

261
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:28,000
Report me to the police?

262
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:31,000
Go ahead.

263
00:15:31,133 --> 00:15:33,800
It's easy to tell them
that you were my accomplice.

264
00:15:35,233 --> 00:15:36,867
And who was there earlier?

265
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:39,900
Wasn't it you?

266
00:15:40,033 --> 00:15:41,833
I have an alibi.

267
00:15:41,967 --> 00:15:43,600
I was with them.

268
00:15:43,733 --> 00:15:48,333
And they know it benefits me
more if Edward stays alive.

269
00:15:48,467 --> 00:15:50,700
But you still knew
there was a plan, didn't you?

270
00:15:52,267 --> 00:15:54,733
Why didn't you report it
to stop it?

271
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:58,267
So what do you think
they'll think now?

272
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:01,233
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

273
00:16:03,867 --> 00:16:05,967
You bastard!
[SIGHS]

274
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:11,167
If you end up in jail,

275
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:14,433
your life will be completely
ruined.

276
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:17,167
And you'll never get to see
your child again.

277
00:16:18,867 --> 00:16:20,600
Is that what you want?

278
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:23,067
What I want is for you
to leave Edward alone!

279
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:24,600
[CHUCKLES]

280
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:27,033
Leave Edward alone?

281
00:16:27,167 --> 00:16:29,767
I remember the last time
we talked,

282
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:31,333
you couldn't stand him.

283
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:33,733
You should actually be happy

284
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:36,000
that Edward is about
to be finished.

285
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:39,933
Because automatically,
Ashley will be yours.

286
00:16:41,933 --> 00:16:45,200
Don't tell me
you still want your ex?

287
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,700
So what if I still do?

288
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:51,400
Listen to me,

289
00:16:51,533 --> 00:16:55,433
I will never allow your plans
to succeed.

290
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:58,633
I may be small,

291
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:00,700
but I can take you down.

292
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:03,267
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

293
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:10,433
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

294
00:17:12,667 --> 00:17:14,533
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

295
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,767
Thank you, thank you.

296
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:17,200
How are you, Mr. Torrecampo?

297
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:19,667
- Well, I'm good and healthy.
- [CHUCKLES]

298
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,600
- Thank you.
- That's good to hear, Sir.

299
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:23,800
- Congratulations, Sir Edward.
- Thank you.

300
00:17:23,933 --> 00:17:26,767
I see the entire family here,
Ma'am Regina.

301
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:28,967
- Yes.
- I have one quick question.

302
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:32,167
If you could rewrite one chapter
of Torrecampo history,

303
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:33,233
what would it be?

304
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:34,600
The real question should be

305
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:38,167
whether there is any chapter
in my life I would change.

306
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:40,033
The answer is no.

307
00:17:40,167 --> 00:17:41,800
It wouldn't change anything.

308
00:17:41,933 --> 00:17:43,233
After all the scandals

309
00:17:43,367 --> 00:17:45,500
and hardships our family
went through,

310
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:47,267
it only made us stronger.

311
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,967
And whatever storms
may still come,

312
00:17:50,133 --> 00:17:52,033
it will only make us stronger.

313
00:17:52,167 --> 00:17:56,067
- [APPLAUDING]
- [LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

314
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:09,567
- Vien, hello.
- How are you?

315
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:11,700
- Hi.
- [PHONE RINGING]

316
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:14,000
Lalaine,

317
00:18:14,133 --> 00:18:17,667
I don't know if I can enjoy this
party knowing what I know.

318
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:19,267
Is Edward already there?

319
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:22,267
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:18:22,433 --> 00:18:23,533
He's here.

321
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,533
Then what are you waiting for?
Go talk to him.

322
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:27,900
Go to him.

323
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:29,900
What if he doesn't want
to talk to me?

324
00:18:30,033 --> 00:18:33,633
Or worse, if he doesn't believe
what I'm about to say.

325
00:18:33,767 --> 00:18:36,967
Friend, what matters is that
you warn Edward.

326
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:40,100
And that you get ahead
of Aldrin.

327
00:18:40,233 --> 00:18:41,967
All right, thank you.

328
00:18:43,967 --> 00:18:46,700
Thea, I want you to meet
Mrs. Vitales.

329
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:49,967
She is the owner
of Vitasa Heavy Equipment.

330
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:52,767
They are the supplier
of Torrecampo.

331
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:55,800
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

332
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:07,367
Good evening, everyone!

333
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:10,567
Tonight, it's more than
a celebration

334
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:13,133
of our company's milestone.

335
00:19:14,167 --> 00:19:18,600
This is a family celebration.

336
00:19:18,733 --> 00:19:23,233
I am officially welcoming back
my youngest son

337
00:19:23,367 --> 00:19:28,067
as a major shareholder
of Torrecampo Realty.

338
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:31,400
None other than...

339
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:33,500
Edward Torrecampo.

340
00:19:33,633 --> 00:19:37,500
- [APPLAUDING]
- [LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

341
00:19:47,167 --> 00:19:50,733
- [LIGHT MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [APPLAUDING CONTINUES]

342
00:19:53,033 --> 00:19:56,267
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

343
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:03,533
Enjoy this moment, my child.

344
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,000
Enjoy this moment.

345
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:08,067
Thank you, Dad.

346
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,900
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

347
00:20:17,267 --> 00:20:19,300
[CHUCKLES]

348
00:20:19,433 --> 00:20:23,233
Sorry if I'm a bit emotional
right now.

349
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:26,600
I honestly thought

350
00:20:26,733 --> 00:20:29,267
I would never experience
this in my lifetime.

351
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:34,467
<i>Yesterday, I thought it was
my last day.</i>

352
00:20:36,433 --> 00:20:38,000
And I thought...

353
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:43,500
I would never get the chance
to prove myself.

354
00:20:43,633 --> 00:20:47,833
But, Dad, thank you so much

355
00:20:47,967 --> 00:20:50,100
for allowing me to prove myself.

356
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:53,500
For giving me my place back.

357
00:20:55,033 --> 00:20:57,500
I promise I won't waste this.

358
00:21:01,633 --> 00:21:03,900
I am proud to be back.

359
00:21:04,033 --> 00:21:05,467
I am proud to be a Torrecampo.

360
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:09,100
- [APPLAUDING]
- [DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

361
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:21,967
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

362
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:34,133
Edward,

363
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:36,867
a lot of people are looking
for you outside.

364
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,567
They want to talk to you.

365
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:40,700
And you're just hiding here.

366
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,500
I'm just taking a pause.

367
00:21:43,633 --> 00:21:47,300
Everything that happened
is a bit overwhelming.

368
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:52,533
I was so proud of you
on stage earlier.

369
00:21:52,667 --> 00:21:55,967
I saw the old Edward
that I knew.

370
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:57,367
Full of dreams.

371
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,400
You deserve all of this, Edward.

372
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:03,267
Thank you, Marj.

373
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:08,200
I know I keep saying that
over and over.

374
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:12,600
But I know that if you and Paolo
hadn't saved me,

375
00:22:12,733 --> 00:22:15,533
I probably wouldn't have
experienced

376
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:17,467
the applause of so many people.

377
00:22:18,667 --> 00:22:22,100
I honestly thought
it was impossible.

378
00:22:22,233 --> 00:22:25,167
Turns out, I just needed

379
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:27,967
to let go of the one person
who was pulling me down.

380
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:31,100
And that was Thea.

381
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:34,633
You know, Marj,

382
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:36,367
I tried my best.

383
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:38,500
I gave everything.

384
00:22:38,633 --> 00:22:40,800
Because I thought that was...

385
00:22:40,933 --> 00:22:43,667
that was what it took
for our marriage not to fail.

386
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:47,900
But Thea was the one who kept
destroying it over and over.

387
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:52,067
She made it very difficult
for me

388
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,600
to love her completely.

389
00:22:54,767 --> 00:22:56,300
I just feel regret.

390
00:22:57,467 --> 00:23:03,333
I regret the many years I wasted
in a toxic relationship.

391
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:08,133
Thea made me believe
that I was a loser,

392
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:12,167
that I was worthless every time
I made a mistake.

393
00:23:13,433 --> 00:23:15,033
She never encouraged me.

394
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,133
She never comforted me.

395
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:23,600
She never cheered for me.

396
00:23:25,267 --> 00:23:26,433
Unlike you, Marj.

397
00:23:29,933 --> 00:23:31,433
You know,

398
00:23:31,567 --> 00:23:33,733
I regret marrying Thea.

399
00:23:33,867 --> 00:23:38,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

400
00:23:39,967 --> 00:23:41,567
All these years,

401
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:43,900
I was just pretending
to be a husband.

402
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:48,167
I was pretending to be happy.

403
00:23:51,033 --> 00:23:53,267
I endured a toxic relationship.

404
00:23:54,333 --> 00:23:56,000
But you know what, deep inside,

405
00:23:57,067 --> 00:23:59,300
I didn't know
if I truly loved her.

406
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:02,933
I thought I did.

407
00:24:04,767 --> 00:24:06,100
But I guess I was just...

408
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:09,833
so eager to have someone
who wanted me.

409
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:13,433
To not be alone.

410
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:17,233
Because all my life,

411
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,433
I felt like I was alone.

412
00:24:27,033 --> 00:24:28,833
So you didn't really love her,

413
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:31,967
why did you marry her?

414
00:24:35,533 --> 00:24:38,133
Because I was so desperate
to erase you, Marj.

415
00:24:41,033 --> 00:24:42,400
I thought back then

416
00:24:44,133 --> 00:24:48,767
that if I had another woman
beside me in bed,

417
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:51,133
I could erase your image
from my mind.

418
00:24:54,133 --> 00:24:56,667
I used her to run away
from the truth.

419
00:24:58,667 --> 00:25:00,467
But the truth can't be escaped.

420
00:25:02,700 --> 00:25:03,733
Thea?

421
00:25:05,233 --> 00:25:09,400
She was the biggest mistake
I made in my life.

422
00:25:12,433 --> 00:25:14,200
That's why, Marj, you know,

423
00:25:15,767 --> 00:25:18,967
that's probably why I feel
so light right now.

424
00:25:19,100 --> 00:25:20,033
I'm just...

425
00:25:21,067 --> 00:25:22,067
I'm just so happy

426
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:24,567
that Thea is no longer
in Ashley's and my life.

427
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:27,800
That there's no one left
holding me back

428
00:25:27,933 --> 00:25:29,367
from reaching my potential.

429
00:25:31,033 --> 00:25:32,400
That I'm finally free

430
00:25:32,533 --> 00:25:34,367
and I've been given a chance

431
00:25:35,867 --> 00:25:37,967
to correct all my mistakes.

432
00:25:41,067 --> 00:25:42,367
Thank you, Marj.

433
00:25:43,933 --> 00:25:45,333
Thank you for everything.

434
00:25:45,467 --> 00:25:48,933
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

435
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:03,433
My child,
I just want to thank you.

436
00:26:03,567 --> 00:26:07,033
Thank you for believing in me
and for loving me.

437
00:26:07,167 --> 00:26:08,600
As if I were your real father.

438
00:26:08,767 --> 00:26:10,333
You're my father.

439
00:26:10,467 --> 00:26:11,500
Regina.

440
00:26:11,633 --> 00:26:13,933
As long as that woman
is still breathing,

441
00:26:14,067 --> 00:26:15,700
I will not stop.

442
00:26:15,833 --> 00:26:18,867
To complete my revenge
against her,

443
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,567
I will finish her.

444
00:26:20,700 --> 00:26:23,167
I will kill Regina.

445
00:26:23,300 --> 00:26:25,267
I've been knocking
on mom and grandmother's door

446
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,400
for a while now.

447
00:26:26,533 --> 00:26:28,500
It seems like
they're not inside.

448
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:32,667
You have some nerve, Edward.

449
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:35,133
You're not even close to Marj.

450
00:26:35,267 --> 00:26:38,567
And you will never be like her.

451
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:41,933
Don't expect that I'll ever
get back together with you.

452
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:43,633
Because leaving you

453
00:26:43,767 --> 00:26:49,000
was the best decision
that I made in my entire life.

454
00:26:49,133 --> 00:26:52,900
We have no one else to rely on
but each other.

455
00:26:53,933 --> 00:26:55,033
Edward!

456
00:26:55,167 --> 00:26:58,400
[AMBULANCE SIREN WAILING]
